latestPosts.caption:
🏃‍♀️With a passion for competition and constantly striving for excellence, Safira Halani naturally gravitated toward the sporting world. Safira is now gearing up to represent Team Canada at the #GEFestival, and is our feature for #TalentTuesday.

Beyond competitions, the results of hard work keep her reaching for more. “It's about more than playing or competing; it's about constantly striving to be better, to challenge myself, and to contribute to something bigger than myself.”

During the year she can be seen participating in competitions across the globe. From North America’s Around the Bay 15km race to Nike’s After Dark Tour in India, she’s looking to train harder and push herself further. “Tough training sessions are where champions are forged” believes Safira. “I focus on the process and the small victories within each session,” she says. “Even on tough days, pushing through and completing the work builds mental toughness.”

A lot of Safira’s mental resilience can be credited to her mother. “She raised us to be self-sufficient, and to never settle for less than the best. She taught me that I could do anything so long as I did it the right way—working hard, working smart and working together.”

“My goals for the Festival are to perform at my best and inspire others, engage meaningfully with other participants in different disciplines, share my experiences, and ultimately represent my country and Inshallah make Canada, my family, team, friends, community and supporters proud,” she says. "If there is one thing I'm looking forward to its meeting people from all walks of life. In the past I have made some pretty amazing connections with people from around the world."

From being in the sporting world for many years, Safira shares the importance of ensuring you have a passion for your craft and finding the joy in every process it involves. She shares: “There will be highs and lows, and some really low lows, but dedication, discipline, and a willingness to learn are crucial. Surround yourself with positive influences, listen to your coaches, ask them questions, and never stop believing in your potential.” 

📷 Ikhwan Allani. Read more at the link in our bio

latestPosts.caption: What a night in Mumbai! The @nike After Dark Tour was such an incredible experience, from that feeling of running freely in a safe space to the power packed performance by @jonitamusic afterwards. So much appreciation for @nikerunning and their dedication to making running accessible and safe for all women. Having the opportunity to meet and connect with all the female powerhouses in that space was immaculate! For many it was their first 10K, some their first run EVER, and others just another notch on the belt. But for all of us together, the experience was memorable and one of a kind! Still buzzing from that post-run high! 😊 SO grateful for the invite (s/o @kranti.s ) 🙏🏽 definitely worth the trip adjustment to Mumbai #NikeMumbai #AfterDarkRun #WomensEmpowerment #RunningCommunity #jonitagandhi #jonita
